{"action": "input", "code": "def is_blue_pixel_reached_top(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function checks if the blue pixel has reached the top of the grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A boolean value indicating if the blue pixel has reached the top of the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return blue in input_grid[0]\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    flag = is_blue_pixel_reached_top(input_grid)\n    while not flag:\n        copy_blue_pixel_right_up(input_grid)\n        copy_blue_pixel_left_up(input_grid)\n    return input_grid\ndef copy_blue_pixel_right_up(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function copies the blue pixel right-up until it reaches the right grid boundary.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pos = np.where(input_grid == blue)\n    row, col = (blue_pos[0][0], blue_pos[1][0])\n    while col < input_grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        if row > 0:\n            input_grid[row, col] = grey\n            row -= 1\n        col += 1\n        input_grid[row, col] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef copy_blue_pixel_left_up(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function copies the blue pixel left-up until it reaches the left grid boundary.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pos = np.where(input_grid == blue)\n    row, col = (blue_pos[0][0], blue_pos[1][0])\n    while col > 0:\n        if row > 0:\n            input_grid[row, col] = grey\n            row -= 1\n        col -= 1\n        input_grid[row, col] = blue\n    return input_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray: \n    flag = `Is blue pixel reach the top`(input_grid)\n    while(not flag):\n        `Keep copying blue pixel right-up until reach right grid boundary, the original blue points keep blue`(input_grid)\n        `Keep copying blue pixel left-up until reach left grid boundary, the original blue point keep blue`(input_grid)\n    return input_grid", "gpt_code": "def is_blue_pixel_reached_top(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function checks if the blue pixel has reached the top of the grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A boolean value indicating if the blue pixel has reached the top of the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    return blue in input_grid[0]\ndef copy_blue_pixel_right_up(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function copies the blue pixel right-up until it reaches the right grid boundary.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pos = np.where(input_grid == blue)\n    row, col = (blue_pos[0][0], blue_pos[1][0])\n    while col < input_grid.shape[1] - 1:\n        if row > 0:\n            input_grid[row, col] = grey\n            row -= 1\n        col += 1\n        input_grid[row, col] = blue\n    return input_grid\ndef copy_blue_pixel_left_up(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function copies the blue pixel left-up until it reaches the left grid boundary.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    blue_pos = np.where(input_grid == blue)\n    row, col = (blue_pos[0][0], blue_pos[1][0])\n    while col > 0:\n        if row > 0:\n            input_grid[row, col] = grey\n            row -= 1\n        col -= 1\n        input_grid[row, col] = blue\n    return input_grid", "holes": {"is_blue_pixel_reached_top": "Is blue pixel reach the top", "copy_blue_pixel_right_up": "Keep copying blue pixel right-up until reach right grid boundary, the 